Total People is a lightweb universal client for any People instance. 
This application does not collect any Personal data from its users. 

All users have validated related Instance policy (CGU) before creating their account. Please refer to this document for further details.

Total People uses Oauth
OAuth is a registration and authentication service provided by hosted People instances that collects various types of Data as specified in the privacy policy of the hosted service. 
Connection to user's instance uses standard HTTPS encryption.

Data from/to Instance is only stored on user's device for visualization and caching purpose and is never sent to any third party plateform.

People have been originaly developped by Total and this service is now Opensource and available for everyone. Please, contribute to the OpenSource code : https://github.com/totaldigital/People
